[Nouns] moisture; moistness; humidity, humectation; madefaction, dew; serein; marsh [more]; hygrometry, hygrometer.
[Verbs] moisten, wet; humect, humectate; sponge, damp, bedew; imbue, imbrue, infiltrate, saturate; soak, drench (water) [more].
be moist; not have a dry thread; perspire (exude) [more].
[Adjectives] moist, damp; watery [more]; madid, roric; undried, humid, sultry, wet, dank, luggy, dewy; roral, rorid; roscid; juicy.
wringing wet, soaking wet; wet through to the skin; saturated, like a wet rat.
swashy, soggy, dabbled; reeking, dripping, soaking, soft, sodden, sloppy, muddy; swampy (marshy) [more]; irriguous.
